08 Mar 2010 15:35






As has been said, the concept (object we never built, whose intensity is gradually ratcheting up) is interesting but the effects leave a lot to be desired. Why would the Foundation bother causing mass insanity when it could make people vanish, or just freakin' shoot them?

Does this even need to be a weapon? What if, instead, it was a tool for some kind of weird terrain engineering, uprooting whole landscapes into Seussian parodies at high intensities? What if it were an amnesia ray, useful for controlling large-scale confidentiality breaches (and less selective at higher intensities, possibly even implanting memories that cause some [DATA EXPUNGED] when you crank it up to Keter)?

This could be really good; it just isn't yet.








